sql:
SELECT action_taken, COUNT(*) AS count_of_transitions
FROM state_transitions
GROUP BY action_taken;

external_knowledge:
'YourStateName' should be replaced with the actual name of the target state of interest; 
The date range specified ('2022-01-01' and '2022-01-31') indicates the query focuses on the month of January 2022; 
This query is useful for analyzing the frequency of certain actions and state transitions within a specific state in a given time frame.
